&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since 2019, the concept used refers to the SDGs metadata where households are said to have access to improved sanitation if the household has a defecation facility which is used alone or with certain (limited) households or in communal toilets, using type of goose neck toilet, and the final disposal place for feces in a septic tank or MCK Communal or it could be in a hole in the ground if in a rural area.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;*)Backcasting&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Notes:&lt;br /&gt;a. In 2000 Susenas enumeration was not done in NAD (Aceh) and Maluku Province &lt;br /&gt;b. In 2001 Susenas enumeration was not done in NAD (Aceh) Province &lt;br /&gt;c. For Aceh, Maluku, Maluku Utara, and Papua Province, Susenas 2002 enumeration was only done in the provincial capital&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;d. Since 2019, the concept used refers to the SDGs metadata where households are said to have access to improved sanitation if the household has a defecation facility which is used alone or with certain (limited) households or in communal toilets, using type of goose neck toilet, and the final disposal place for feces in a septic tank or MCK Comunal or it could be in a hole in the ground if the area where he lives is in a rural area.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source: National Socioeconomic Survey, BPS-Statistics Indonesia&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source: BPS-RI, Susenas 2009-2022&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since 2019, the concept used refers to the SDGs metadata where households are said to have access to improved water, that is, if the main drinking water sources used are tap, protected water and rainwater. Protected water includes boreholes / pumps, protected wells and protected springs. Households that use drinking water sources in the form of bottled water are categorized as having access to improved drinking water if the water sources for bathing / washing come from taps, boreholes / pumps, protected wells, protected springs, and rainwater.
	&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;*) Backasting&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source: BPS-RI, Susenas &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since 2019, households are classified as having access to shelter / livable housing if they meet 4 (four) criteria, namely:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1) adequate living space of at least 7.2 m2 per capita (sufficient living space)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2) have access to improved drinking water&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3) have access to improved sanitation&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4) durablelity housing, namely the widest roof in the form of concrete / tile / zinc / wood / shingle; the widest wall in the form of woven bamboo / wire, wood / planks and wooden sticks of plaster; and the largest floor in the form of marble / granite / ceramic / parquet / vinyl / carpet / tiles / tiles / terrazzo / wood / board / cement / red brick.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Source: BPS-RI, Susenas March&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2015-2018 uses a concept that refers to the SDGs metadata published in 2017 where households are said to have access to improved sanitation services if the household has a defecation facility that is used alone or with certain (limited) households, using type of goose neck toilet, and a place for final disposal of feces in a septic tank or IPAL.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Since 2019 the concept used refers to the latest SDGs metadata where households are said to have access to improved sanitation services if the household has a defecation facility which is used alone or with certain (limited) households or in communal toilets, using a type of goose neck toilet, and the final disposal site for feces in a septic tank or IPAL or it could be in a hole in the ground if in a rural area&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

