&lt;p&gt;
Districts / cities that do not display the value of the Special Stunting Handling Index (IKPS) are areas that have the IKPS compiler indicator with a Relative Standard Error above 25 percent.
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
IKPS is an index compiled to meet the target of Disbursement Linked Indicators (DLI) 8 Cooperation Agreement between the Government of Indonesia and the World Bank. IKPS at the national and provincial levels is formed from 6 (six) dimensions, namely the dimensions of health, nutrition, housing, food, education, and social protection. IKPS at the district / city level is formed from 5 (five) dimensions, namely the dimensions of health, nutrition, housing, education, and social protection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
IKPS is in the form of numbers on a scale of 1-100. Changes in the IKPS indicate a change in indicators related to stunting. IKPS is a proxy used to see the development of various indicators related to stunting. Apart from the March 2018 National Socio-Economic Survey (Susenas), specifically for 2018 the data used to compile the IKPS also uses the March 2018 Susenas integration data and 2018 Basic Health Research (Riskesdas).
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
Resulted from: National Socio-Economic Survey (Susenas) March 2018, National Socio-Economic Survey (Susenas) March 2019.
&lt;/p&gt;

